ğŸ¯ Key Difference: Docker vs Maven Repositories
Aspect	Docker Images	Maven Repositories
Scope	Complete environment	Only Java libraries
Content	OS + Runtime + App + Config	Just .jar files
Portability	Runs anywhere with Docker	Needs existing Java env
Isolation	Complete isolation	Shares host environment
Use Case	Deploy applications	Manage Java dependencies
Real World Analogy:

    Maven Repository = ğŸ“š Library (just books)

    Docker Image = ğŸ  Complete furnished house (building + furniture + utilities)

Companies use BOTH:

    Use Maven to build Java applications

    Use Docker to package and run those applications consistently

This is why modern development teams can't live without Docker - it eliminates environment inconsistencies forever! ğŸš€

